      "writtenOn": "2020-06-09T15:57:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It says the number of descriptors, not number of ranges. The number of descriptors in both cases adds up to fNumSamplers. The validator is not having any issues with it.\n\n\"The number of source descriptors (to copy from), specified as a set of descriptor ranges, must equal the number of destination descriptors (to copy to), specified as a separate set of descriptor ranges. The source and destination ranges do not otherwise have to line up. For example, a sparse set of descriptors could be copied to a contiguous destination, vice versa, or in some combination.\"",
